            </p>
          </div>
          <div class="placeholder-card">
            <p style="margin: 0; font-style: italic;">ðŸŽ¯ Game #3 planned</p>
            <p style="margin: 8px 0 0; font-size: 0.9em;">
              More games on the way!
            </p>
          </div>
        </div>
      )
    }

    <h2>Latest devlogs</h2>
    <div class="grid">
      {
        posts.length > 0 ? (
          posts.map((post) => (
            <a class="card" href={post.filePath}>
              {post.title} â†’
            </a>
          ))
        ) : (
          <div class="placeholder-card">
            <p style="margin: 0; font-style: italic;">
              ðŸš§ No devlogs yet...
            </p>
            <p style="margin: 8px 0 0; font-size: 0.9em;">
              Check back soon for updates!
            </p>
          </div>
        )
      }
    </div>

    <div class="challenge-info">
      <h2>The Challenge</h2>
      <p>
        The 20 Games Challenge is a year-long journey to build 20 complete
        games, focusing on finishing projects and learning new skills. Each game
        is designed to explore different mechanics, genres, and technical
        challenges.
      </p>

      <p>
        Every game is built with web deployment in mind - meaning fast load
        times, efficient bundles, and playable experiences that work across
        devices. The goal isn't just to make games, but to make them accessible.
      </p>

      <h3>Rules & Constraints</h3>
      <h4>Challenge Rules</h4>
      <ul>
        <li>
          <strong>No tutorials:</strong> Don't follow full tutorials; quick Q&A is
          fine
        </li>
        <li>
          <strong>Constrain yourself:</strong> Set limits and move on â€” polish later
        </li>
        <li><strong>Be flexible:</strong> Adapt and change plans as needed</li>
      </ul>
      <h4>Personal Rules</h4>
      <ul>
        <li>
          <strong>Ship it:</strong> Every game must be playable and "done"
        </li>
        <li>
          <strong>Web-first:</strong> All games should run in browsers when possible
